        <!-- Main Content -->
        <main class="main-content">
            <div class="content-wrapper">
                <!-- Left Content -->
                <div class="content-left">
                    <div class="content-section">
                        <h2>What is the PTE Exam?</h2>
                        <p>The Pearson Test of English (PTE) is an international standardized test designed to assess the English language proficiency of non-native speakers who wish to study abroad, work, or migrate to English-speaking countries. PTE scores are widely accepted for university admissions, visa applications, and job placements.</p>
                        <div class="highlight-box">
                            <p>Manya – The Princeton Review’s PTE prep is an extensive program designed to help you achieve your dream of studying or settling in an English-speaking country. With expert trainers and a structured curriculum, Manya ensures you are fully prepared for the exam.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="content-section">
                        <h2>PTE Prep Offerings</h2>
                        <div class="highlight-box">
                            <table>
                                <thead>
                                    <tr>
                                        <th>Tutoring</th>
                                        <th>Study Material</th>
                                    </tr>
                                </thead>
                                <tbody>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td>1 Hour of PTE Orientation</td>
                                        <td>Portal access for interactive classes and structured self-practice</td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td>3 hours of Diagnostic Tests</td>
                                        <td>80 sectional tests of Reading, Writing, Listening, and Speaking</td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td>Full-length Mock tests</td>
                                        <td>10 full-length mock tests</td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td>42 hours of learning and Practice</td>
                                        <td>Interactive English challenge zone</td>
                                    </tr>
                                </tbody>
                            </table>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="content-section">
                        <h2>PTE Exam Preparation</h2>
                        <p>Candidates must prove their English language proficiency by taking an English test, regardless of their desired university or course. PTE Academic is a worldwide English language test that is accepted by hundreds of schools. For the benefit of our test takers, we will discuss the PTE preparation material that is available online.</p>
                        <div class="highlight-box">
                            <h3>Preparation Material for PTE Test</h3>
                            <p>Each subject can be mastered in a few days if you pay full attention and concentration, as the test checks your regular communication skills in the English language. For better preparation, you can always use the online videos and tutorials available on the internet, as well as mock papers.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="content-section">
                        <h2>PTE Exam Sections</h2>
                        <div class="highlight-box">
                            <table>
                                <thead>
                                    <tr>
                                        <th>Section</th>
                                        <th>Duration</th>
                                    </tr>
                                </thead>
                                <tbody>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td>Reading Section</td>
                                        <td>29-30 minutes</td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td>Listening Section</td>
                                        <td>30-43 minutes</td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td>Speaking and Writing Section</td>
                                        <td>54-67 minutes</td>
                                    </tr>
                                </tbody>
                            </table>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="content-section">
                        <h2>PTE Exam Preparation Tips</h2>
                        <div class="highlight-box">
                            <h3>Tips for Writing Section</h3>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Use good vocabulary and grammar to score high.</li>
                                <li>Keep responses concise (35–45 words).</li>
                                <li>Pay attention to punctuation and capitalization.</li>
                            </ul>
                            <h3>Tips for Listening Section</h3>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Listen actively to English songs, movies, and TV shows.</li>
                                <li>Read questions before listening to the audio.</li>
                                <li>Stay focused until the end of the audio.</li>
                            </ul>
                            <h3>Tips for Speaking Section</h3>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Practice daily with tongue twisters.</li>
                                <li>Use rising and falling tones appropriately.</li>
                                <li>Focus on keywords if you forget the text.</li>
                            </ul>
                            <h3>Tips for Reading Section</h3>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Understand the passage’s core message.</li>
                                <li>Use the rule of elimination to find the correct answer.</li>
                                <li>Practice paraphrasing to improve comprehension.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="content-section">
                        <h2>Best Books for PTE</h2>
                        <div class="highlight-box">
                            <ul>
                                <li><strong>The Official Guide to PTE Academic by Pearson PTE Academic:</strong> Includes authentic test questions and strategies.</li>
                                <li><strong>Aspire C1 Practice Tests with Key:</strong> Contains four complete tests with tips and sample answers.</li>
                                <li><strong>PTE Practice Tests Plus with Key, Vol 1 and 2:</strong> Offers comprehensive study tips and audio CDs.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Right Content (Form) -->
                <div class="content-right">
                    <form class="enquiry-form" id="enquiryForm" action="/submit-pteTest" method="POST">
                        <h3>Planning to study abroad?</h3>
                        <p>Get free 1-on-1 counselling with our experts</p>
            
                        <div class="form-group">
                            <input type="text" id="firstName" name="firstName" required>
                            <label for="firstName">First Name</label>
                        </div>
            
                        <div class="form-group">
                            <input type="text" id="lastName" name="lastName" required>
                            <label for="lastName">Last Name</label>
                        </div>
            
                        <div class="form-group">
                            <input type="email" id="email" name="email" required>
                            <label for="email">Email</label>
                        </div>
            
                        <div class="form-group">
                            <input type="tel" id="mobile" name="mobile" pattern="[0-9]{10}" required>
                            <label for="mobile">Mobile No. (10 digits)</label>
                        </div>
            
                        <div class="form-group">
                            <select id="program" name="program" required>
                                <option value="">Select Program</option>
                                <option value="GMAT">GMAT</option>
                                <option value="GRE">GRE</option>
                                <option value="IELTS">IELTS</option>
                            </select>
                            <label for="program">Select Program</label>
                        </div>
                        <div class="form-group">
                            <select id="mode" name="mode" required>
                                <option value="">Select Mode</option>
                                <option value="Classroom">Classroom Coaching</option>
                                <option value="Online">Online Coaching</option>
                            </select>
                            <label for="mode">Select Mode</label>
                        </div>
            
                        <div class="form-group">
                            <select id="city" name="city" required>
                                <option value="">Select City</option>
                                <option value="Noida">Noida</option>
                                <option value="Delhi">Delhi</option>
                                <option value="Gurgaon">Gurgaon</option>
                            </select>
                            <label for="city">Select City</label>
                        </div>
            
                        <div class="checkbox-group">
                            <input type="checkbox" id="authorize" name="authorize" required>
                            <label for="authorize">I authorize Manya - The Princeton Review to contact me even if my number is registered with DND to assist with my enquiry and get regular updates through SMS/Whatsapp.</label>
                        </div>
            
                        <button type="submit" class="submit-btn">Submit</button>
                    </form>
                </div>
            </div>
